adjectives.description: fumish (comparative more fumish, superlative most fumish)

entries.meaning: (obsolete) Pertaining to fumes or smoke. [16th–17th c.]
examples: Notwithstanding, out of the relicks of our miseries, time and experience had brought that Country to a great happinesse, had they not so much doated on their Tabacco, on whose fumish foundation there is small stability  […]
